{
  "texts": [
    "While the majority of the ML community are moving towards diffusion and other flow-matching based models due to the success of models like StableDiffusion [34] in other domains, this article finds in favor of GANs when applied to turbulence.Outline.",
    "The remainder of the paper is structured as follows.",
    "Section 2 gives a review on key studies in the field using VAE, GAN or DDPM for applications of turbulence modeling.",
    "In section 3 we describe our specific implementation of the VAE, GAN, and DDPM along with a summary of the theoretical foundations of these models.",
    "Section 4 offers a brief description of the experimental and numerical datasets used in this study."
  ]
}